{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TMZJNFiAVPXRX2nstXvkfr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is:\n1. crdb-cluster-2 is running in secure mode (with `--certs-dir`) and it's trying to reach the other nodes\n2. But crdb-cluster-0 and crdb-cluster-1 are still running in insecure mode (with `--insecure`)\n3. When a secure node tries to connect to an insecure node, they can't communicate because the TLS handshake fails\n\nThis is the fundamental problem with rolling restart for an insecure-to-secure migration in CockroachDB. The nodes can't be mixed between secure and insecure modes.\nThe 503 readiness probe failure is because the node can't establish quorum with the insecure nodes, so the health endpoint returns 503 when the node isn't ready to join the cluster. CockroachDB doesn't support mixed secure and insecure clusters, so I need to scale down all nodes simultaneously before upgrading them together to secure mode. The issue is that crdb-cluster-2 can't join because it's trying to communicate securely with nodes that aren't listening for TLS, so the rolling update gets stuck. I need to restart all three pods at once rather than one at a time—either by scaling to zero and back up to three, or by deleting all the pods simultaneously to force the StatefulSet to recreate them with the new secure configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1196,"cache_read_input_tokens":39952,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1196},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a95feb31-df34-4110-9758-5a7d16867dcd","uuid":"efc17e11-0ed0-4113-8752-eaf775f65c00","request_id":"req_011CcemogJ96EFxQfnfgYhzt"}
