{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QoupUdxQQbQKL9XxpWJKGt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Only crdb-cluster-0 is starting but not ready. The StatefulSet creates pods in order (0, 1, 2) and only proceeds to the next once the previous one is ready. But crdb-cluster-0 can't become ready because it can't form a cluster by itself (readiness probe requires the node to be ready and serving, which requires cluster quorum).\n\nThis is the classic CockroachDB bootstrap problem with Kubernetes StatefulSets and `OrderedReady` pod management policy. With `OrderedReady`, pod 1 won't start until pod 0 is ready, and pod 0 can't be ready until it can reach quorum.\nThere's also the issue of leftover data from the previous insecure cluster still sitting on the PVCs. When switching to secure mode, CockroachDB should handle the existing data fine since it doesn't encrypt at rest—security only affects network connections—but the readiness probe might still fail for other reasons during the transition.\n\nThe real bottleneck is that the StatefulSet uses ordered pod startup, so crdb-cluster-0 starts first and waits for quorum, but pods 1 and 2 never start because pod 0 isn't ready. This creates a deadlock where pod 0 can't achieve quorum without the other pods, and the other pods won't start until pod 0 is ready. The solution would be to switch to parallel pod startup, but that's not something you can change on an existing StatefulSet—it's an immutable field. This creates a deadlock where Pod 0 can't get quorum because the readiness probe keeps failing on the `/health?ready=1` endpoint, preventing Pods 1 and 2 from ever starting. The original cluster must have had a different initialization mechanism. CockroachDB distinguishes between `/health` for liveness checks and `/health?ready=1` for readiness, and with a low failure threshold, the pod gets marked as not ready too quickly. 't completed bootstrapping or isn't serving SQL yet. The original cluster started successfully with a 10-second initial delay and 2 failure threshold, giving it 20 seconds total before failing. Since the PVCs still contain data from the previous insecure cluster run, the nodes should recognize each other when they restart, but there's a secure/insecure mismatch in the persistent data causing the issue.\n\nActually, CockroachDB doesn't embed security mode in the data itself, so that's not the problem. The real issue is that when a node starts in secure mode for the first time after running insecure, it needs to establish TLS trust, but the old insecure cluster data doesn't have that information. I should check the actual logs from crdb-cluster-0 to see what's really going on.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2220,"cache_read_input_tokens":42263,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2220},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a95feb31-df34-4110-9758-5a7d16867dcd","uuid":"8676f807-3f0e-4b05-a03a-9f3e7fff4cce","request_id":"req_011CcenM5aynGp4sVByRJc9b"}
