{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JVZ2rVv3EDdgxtd92obA34","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 3 pods are running and ready. Now let me verify the two goal conditions:\n\n1. Insecure access should be rejected\n2. Secure access should succeed\n\nAlso, I need to copy the client root certs into the pod so the secure access command can work. The command `./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs` will look for client certs in `/cockroach/cockroach-certs`. The node certs secret only has `ca.crt`, `node.crt`, and `node.key`. For client authentication, the pod needs `client.root.crt` and `client.root.key` as well.\nThe certs directory mounted at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs` contains the node certificates from the secret, but CockroachDB also needs the client root certificates (`client.root.crt` and `client.root.key`) in that same directory for the root user to authenticate when connecting via the SQL client.\n\nI should update the `crdb-certs` secret to include both the node certificates and the client root certificates, then restart the pods so they pick up the updated secret.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1070,"cache_read_input_tokens":49337,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1070},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a95feb31-df34-4110-9758-5a7d16867dcd","uuid":"1a6cae7a-c7fb-463a-a44c-37a6f9e79c3f","request_id":"req_011CcenXjW3r4wJ7YA4qJxiC"}
